    <p>My approach is to have you read <b>primary sources</b> like the <a
        href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/">HTML specification</a> and the <a
        href="http://docs.python.org/reference/">Python Language Reference</a>
    documentation, and not just secondary sources such as tutorials and
    &ldquo;howto&rdquo; books. You&rsquo;re a beginner to programming, not
    English. In addition, we&rsquo;ll work through Eric Raymond&rsquo;s book,
    <i>The Cathedral and the Bazaar</i>, which will orient you to the culture
    surrounding the technology. You&rsquo;ll do a lot of reading and hacking,
    guided by yours truly, and by the end of the course you&rsquo;ll feel
    confident in your inside-out knowledge of how the Web works, and
    you&rsquo;ll be empowered to continue learning and hacking.</p>

